        "# Race/Ethnicity Breakdown\n",
        "This section shows the race/ethnic demographic distribution for every city in Orange County."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "id": "251641a4",
      "metadata": {

      },
      "source": [
        "```{margin} To calculate raw population numbers, multiple the percentage of the population by the total population.\n",
        "\n",
        "For example, to find the total population of American Indian / Alaska Natives in Orange County, multiply the county population of 3,168,044 by 0.2% (or 0.002). There are 6,336 residents in Orange County who are American Indian / Alaska Native.\n",
        "\n",
        "Remember, these numbers are based on 2015-2019 ACS data, not the 2020 Census results (see the Methodology section for more information on data sources).\n",
        "```"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "id": "ddc46062",
      "metadata": {

      },
      "source": [
        "## Summary\n",
        "In raw population numbers, the Cities of Huntington Beach, Anaheim, and Garden Grove each have the highest populations of residents who are \u003Cb\u003EAmerican Indian / Alaska Native\u003C/b\u003E (non-Hispanic) (over 500 people), and the City of Garden Grove has the next highest population (over 330 people).\n",
        "\n",
        "The City of Irvine has the highest population of residents who are \u003Cb\u003EAsian\u003C/b\u003E (non-Hispanic) (over 115,000 people), and the Cities of Garden Grove and Anaheim each have the next highest populations (over 55,000 people). \u003Cb\u003EAt a disaggregated level:\u003C/b\u003E\n",
        "\n",
        "The City of Irvine has the highest population of residents who are \u003Cb\u003EAsian Indian\u003C/b\u003E (including Hispanic/Latino origin) (over 15,000 people), and the Cities of Anaheim, Tustin, and Buena Park each have the next highest populations (over 3,000 people).\n",
        "\n",
        "The City of Irvine has the highest population of residents who are \u003Cb\u003EChinese\u003C/b\u003E (including Hispanic/Latino origin) (over 45,000 people), and the Cities of Anaheim, Fullerton, and Yorba Linda each have the next highest populations (over 5,000 residents).\n",
        "\n",
        "The City of Anaheim has the highest population of residents who are \u003Cb\u003EFilipino\u003C/b\u003E (including Hispanic/Latino origin) (almost 15,000 people), and the Cities of Irvine and Buena Park each have the next highest populations (over 7,000 people).\n",
        "\n",
        "The City of Irvine has the highest population of residents who are \u003Cb\u003EJapanese\u003C/b\u003E (including Hispanic/Latino origin) (almost 8,000 people), and the Cities of Huntington Beach and Anaheim each have the next highest populations (over 2,000 people).\n",
        "\n",
        "The Cities of Irvine and Fullerton each have the highest populations of residents who are \u003Cb\u003EKorean\u003C/b\u003E (including Hispanic/Latino origin) (over 16,000 people), and the City of Buena Park has the next highest population (over 9,000 people).\n",
        "\n",
        "The City of Garden Grove has the highest population of residents who are \u003Cb\u003EVietnamese\u003C/b\u003E (including Hispanic/Latino origin) (over 55,000 people), and the Cities of Westminster and Santa Ana each have the next highest populations (over 25,000 people).\n",
        "\n",
        "The Cities of Irvine and Anaheim each have the highest populations of residents who are \u003Cb\u003E“Other Asian”\u003C/b\u003E (including Hispanic/Latino origin) (over 6,000 people), and the Cities of Santa Ana and Garden Grove each have the next highest populations (over 4,000 people).\n",
        "\n",
        "The City of Anaheim has the highest population of residents who are \u003Cb\u003EBlack / African American\u003C/b\u003E (non-Hispanic) (over 8,000 people), and the Cities of Irvine, Santa Ana, and Fullerton each have the next highest populations (over 3,000 people).\n",
        "\n",
        "The City of Santa Ana has the highest population of residents who are \u003Cb\u003EHispanic/Latino\u003C/b\u003E of Any Race (over 250,000 people), and the City of Anaheim has the next highest population (over 190,000 people). \u003Cb\u003EAt a disaggregated level:\u003C/b\u003E\n",
        "\n",
        "The City of Santa Ana has the highest population of residents who are \u003Cb\u003EMexican\u003C/b\u003E (over 230,000 people), and the City of Anaheim has the next highest population (over 160,000 people).\n",
        "\n",
        "The City of Anaheim has the highest population of residents who are \u003Cb\u003EPuerto Rican\u003C/b\u003E (over 1,700 people), and the Cities of Irvine and Huntington Beach each have the next highest populations (over 800 people).\n",
        "\n",
        "The Cities of Huntington Beach and Anaheim each have the highest populations of residents who are \u003Cb\u003ECuban\u003C/b\u003E (over 700 people), and the Cities of Tustin and Fullerton each have the next highest populations (over 500 people).\n",
        "\n",
        "The Cities of Anaheim and Santa Ana each have the highest populations of residents who are \u003Cb\u003E“Other Hispanic/Latino”\u003C/b\u003E (over 17,000 people), and the Cities of Irvine and Huntington Beach each have the next highest populations (over 7,000 people).\n",
        "\n",
        "The City of Anaheim has the highest population of residents who are \u003Cb\u003ENative Hawaiian / Pacific Islander\u003C/b\u003E (non-Hispanic) (over 1,400 people), and the City of Costa Mesa has the next highest population (over 900 people).\n",
        "\n",
        "The City of Huntington Beach has the highest population of residents who are \u003Cb\u003E“Some Other Race”\u003C/b\u003E (non-Hispanic) (over 800 people), and the Cities of Santa Ana and Irvine each have the next highest population (over 500 people).\n",
        "\n",
        "The City of Irvine has the highest population of residents who are \u003Cb\u003E“Two or More Races”\u003C/b\u003E (non-Hispanic) (over 11,000 people) and the City of Huntington Beach has the next highest population (almost 8,000 people).\n",
        "\n",
        "Lastly, the Cities of Huntington Beach and Irvine each have the highest populations of residents who are \u003Cb\u003EWhite\u003C/b\u003E (non-Hispanic) (over 110,000 people), and the City of Anaheim has the next highest population (almost 85,000 people)."
